   "source": [
    "## Function basics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We have already seen a number of functions built into python that let us do useful things to strings, collections and numbers etc. For example **`print()`** or **`len()`** which is passed some kind of sequence object and returns the length of the sequence.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the general form of a function; it takes some input _arguments_ and returns some output based on the supplied arguments.\n",
    "\n",
    "The arguments to a function, if any, are supplied in parentheses and the result of the function _call_ is the result of evaluating the function.\n"
   ]
  },
